obo:GO_0003674  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_681  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: * GFP-Triad3A colocalized with clathrin-DsRed in dendritic shafts and spines of hippocam- pal neurons (Figure 6A) but not with the postsynaptic density marker Homer-DsRed (Figure 6B).\n* Endogenous Triad3A in dendritic spines tightly overlapped with clathrin- DsRed within a subdomain of the spine (Figure 6C)\n* Immunogold electron microscopy (EM) of rat CA1 hippocampus in vivo shows Triad3A immunogold labeling near the membrane and on vesicle-like structures in both presynaptic terminals and postsynaptic spines (Figure 6E).\n* (>30%) of gold particles were positioned along the plasma membrane near the PSD. Experimental description: Supp info: Hippocampal neurons were isolated from E18 rat embryos and cultured as previously described (Ehlers, 2000)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2017-10-23" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_681" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

